The paper presents a software platform designed for the topological analysis of scalar data in scientific visualization. It discusses the challenges faced in developing the platform and presents algorithms and software engineering techniques used to address them. The paper is likely to be categorized under computer science sub-categories related to graphics (cs.GR), computer vision (cs.CV), data structures (cs.DS), computational geometry (cs.CG), and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
